    "created_at": "2026-02-07T21:07:25Z",
    "updated_at": "2026-02-07T21:07:25Z",
    "body": "I was recently bitten by this in a different way. My home-manager config failed to activate due to conflict with my profile, which meant that all my packages disappeared from `~/.nix-profile/bin`, including starship, so my prompt died. If it had used the absolute path it would've kept working. But yeah, I see the rationale behind not wanting it to garbage-collect, which is a more likely issue than mine. As well as wanting upgrades without having to re-source the config.\n\nBut I do think it would make sense if, when it was invoked via an explicit path rather than via `$PATH`, it would use the explicit path:\n```\n$ ./target/debug/starship init bash\neval -- \"$($PWD/target/debug/starship init bash --print-full-init)\"\n```\nwhile\n```\n$ starship init bash\neval -- \"$($HOME/.nix-profile/bin/starship init bash --print-full-init)\"\n```",
    "author_association": "NONE",
